description:
How can Adventists reach people in the cities? How can we make an impact on our communities? These questions and more will be answered by Pastor’s Luis Biazotto and Shawn Brace during this week's episode of #ANN In-Depth.

This episode is based on the “Reach the World: I Will Go”  Leadership Objective 2: To strengthen and diversify Adventist outreach in large cities, across the 10/40 Window, among unreached and under-reached people groups, and to non-Christian religions. The focus is for each conference, mission, and region in the 10/40 Window to achieve a demonstrable increase in the number of new believers and for a demonstrable increase in total members and congregations in all urban areas of one million people or more.

OUR GUESTS
Luis Biazotto is Adventist Community Services Director for the Greater New York Conference. The "Wellness on the Go" - Van Ministry (by the ACS) is one of the most effective ways to bring non-Christians to know our church in New York City. 

Shawn Brace is a Pastor at Bangor Seventh-day Adventist Church. He is focused on mission in the community, particularly connecting with the unchurched.
